The idea that the [[types]] in [[type theory]] are (mathematical) _concepts_/_notions_ (i.e. "Begriffe", as in the [formalization dictionary](#Dictionary) above ) is arguably implicit in the original 

* {#MartinLoef73} [[Per Martin-LÃ¶f]], _An intuitionistic theory of types: predicative part_, In Logic Colloquium (1973), ed. H. E. Rose and J. C. Shepherdson (North-Holland, 1974), 73-118. ([web](http://citeseerx.ist.psu.edu/viewdoc/summary?doi=10.1.1.131.926))

